div1.p: As a stated term of the United States Circuit District Court for the District of Washington, Northern Division held at the Court Room in the City of Seattle on Monday the 12th day of June in the year of our Lord one thousand eight hundred and ninety three.
In the matter of Moy Chong on Habeas Corpus.

Now on this 12th day of June, 1892, this matter comes on regularly for hearing upon the petition of the petitioner and the return of the U.S.Marshal, on the writ of habeas corpus is- sued in this cause; petitioner being represented by Marshall K. Snell, Esq., and the United States Marshal being represented by Wm.H Brinker, Esq., United States Attorney, the cause pro- ceeds by the examination of witnesses on behalf of the petition- er until the close thereof, at which time the Court being fully advised in the premises finds that the said petitioner is not unlawfully restrained of his liberty, and it is ordered that the said petition be, and the same is hereby denied and the said petitioner Moy Chong is remanded to the custody of the U.S.Mar- shal to be by him delivered into the custody of the Collector of Customs for the District of Puget Sound, to be by him dealt with as provided by law.
United States District Circuit Court, District of Washington.
In re Moy chong ON Habeas Cor- pus
I hereby certify that the foregoing is a full, true and correct copy of an original order made and entered in the above entitled cause, remanding petitioner
Attest my hand and seal of said Circuit District Court, this 12# day of June A.D. 1893.
In obedience to the commands of the within writ the said Moy Chung has this day been by me delivered into the custody of the Collector of Customs for the District of Puget Sound.
